# Vendored SFML `.gitignore` Configuration

This `.gitignore` file is intended to live **inside the vendored SFML directory** within the repository.

Its goal is to:
- Ignore **all generated build outputs** (objects, binaries, caches)
- Ignore **platform binaries by default**
- **Explicitly allow only the required MSVC x64 extlibs**
- Keep the repository clean while preserving the **exact third-party binaries needed to build on Windows (MSVC x64)**

This approach ensures:
- Reproducible builds
- No accidental platform pollution
- Clear intent about which binaries are allowed and why

---

```gitignore
############################################################
# Vendored SFML (.gitignore)
#
# Purpose:
# - Ignore generated outputs (build/, obj/, cache, etc.)
# - Ignore binaries by default
# - Explicitly allow ONLY required MSVC x64 extlibs
#
# This prevents repository pollution while ensuring
# the build remains self-contained on Windows (MSVC).
############################################################


#############################
# Prerequisites
#############################

# Dependency-generated files
*.d


#############################
# Compiled object files
#############################

*.slo
*.lo
*.o
*.obj


#############################
# Precompiled headers
#############################

*.gch
*.pch


#############################
# Fortran module files
# (included for compatibility/completeness)
#############################

*.mod
*.smod


#############################
# Executables
#############################

*.exe
*.out
*.app


#############################
# Generated build folders
#############################

build/


#############################
# Cache / IDE folders
#############################

.cache/
.vscode/
.idea/


############################################################
# Binary files (ignored by default)
#
# This avoids committing local builds, toolchain outputs,
# or platform-specific binaries by accident.
############################################################

*.so
*.dylib
*.dll
*.lai
*.la
*.a
*.lib


############################################################
# EXCEPTIONS â€” explicitly allowed binaries
#
# These rules override the ignores above and allow ONLY
# the required MSVC x64 runtime and import libraries
# shipped with SFML.
############################################################

# Ensure extlibs directory is always tracked
!extlibs/
!extlibs/**/

# Allow MSVC universal x64 libraries
!extlibs/libs-msvc-universal/
!extlibs/libs-msvc-universal/**/
!extlibs/libs-msvc-universal/x64/
!extlibs/libs-msvc-universal/x64/*.lib

# Allow MSVC x64 runtime DLLs (e.g. OpenAL)
!extlibs/bin/
!extlibs/bin/**/
!extlibs/bin/x64/
!extlibs/bin/x64/*.dll


############################################################
# Explicitly exclude non-target platforms
#
# Even though these are already ignored by default,
# listing them here makes the intent unambiguous.
############################################################

extlibs/libs-android/
extlibs/libs-ios/
extlibs/libs-mingw/
extlibs/libs-msvc/